BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Larisa Kislinskaya] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 17 Jun -- The criminal who on 16 June threw 
a homemade explosive device into the stairwell of the building 
on Molostovykh Street in Moscow which houses one of the sections 
of the Logovaz joint-stock company has been arrested. The 
ITAR-TASS correspondent was told by the Moscow city directorate 
of internal affairs that the man had admitted that that it had 
been a terrorist act directed against Logovaz. 
  According to updated reports, one female LogoVAZ employee 
suffered injuries. 

